Package: sampler
Type: Package
Title: Aggregated and overdispersed sampling
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Bruno Vilela, Ty Tuff, Trevor Fristoe, Edric Gavin, Lucas Jardim, Sara Varela & Carlos Botero.
Maintainer: Bruno Vilela <bvilela@wustl.edu>
Description: Generate aggregated or overdispersed sampling designs for any given phylogenetic tree, spatial points or distance matrix. Results can be used to design experiments/samples, for resample proposes and data bias removal.
License: GPL-2
Encoding: UTF-8
Imports:
    fields,
    ape,
    phangorn,
    picante
Suggests:
    testthat,
    raster,
    adephylo,
    knitr,
    rmarkdown,
    sp,
    maptools
Depends:
    R (>= 3.0),
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1
URL: https://github.com/BrunoVilela/sampler
BugReports: https://github.com/BrunoVilela/sampler
VignetteBuilder: knitr
